Michael Jackson: 30th Anniversary Special

In late November 2001, the CBS television network aired a two-hour 
special in honor of Michael Jackson's thirtieth year as a solo 
entertainer (his first solo single, "Got to Be There", was recorded in
 1971).
 
The show was edited from footage of two separate concerts Michael had 
orchestrated in New York City's Madison Square Garden on September 7 
and September 10 of 2001. The shows sold out in five hours.
